parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The steering wheel is hard to turn
especially at low speeds
making it difficult to park or maneuver in tight spaces. The power steering pump may make a loud whining or squealing noise. The steering wheel may vibrate or shimmy
especially at high speeds.

the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vehicle's security system can allow unauthorized access to the vehicle, leading to theft or vandalism.
